Washim district. Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Washim has released the original budget of Pimpri Khuntia Mangralpir Tap Water Supply Scheme vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. Also, Reference No. Under Section 1, a price as low as Rs 9,89,146 is granted administrative approval. Also, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Washim proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The letter dated 19.7.2024 has been submitted to the government. Reference 3. Under the letter dated 16.7.2024, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Washim.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. The Pimpri Kshetra Mangralpir Tap Water Supply Scheme is being implemented at a cost of Rs. The revised price of 10,42,136 / - (Rupees Ten Lakh forty two thousand one hundred and thirty six only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2024 / Q. No.193 / Papu WRA (E Office 10.-922744)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred annually for implementation of the scheme, its maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or for renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) According to a CAG report in 2013, 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity of bills due to lack of these maintenance repairs. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, the Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for the necessary increase in the water table rate.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
